{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87eb1c5d-447e-435e-a517-9db64666262a","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_uzHP2MnhZYtR6UI3JNjZnj","name":"glob","arguments":{"pattern":"**/*.{nuspec,csproj,nupkg}","path":"/tmp/sv-e67835b9905e4ea1bec40de7be719161"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"/tmp/sv-e67835b9905e4ea1bec40de7be719161"}],"interactionId":"8cf20ffd-3edf-421c-bc41-efed87f298de","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness.\n\nThe template.json is a .NET template configuration file. Let me check what's required and what might be missing:\n\n**Required fields:**\n- `$schema` - missing (not strictly required but highly recommended)\n- `author` ✅\n- `classifications` ✅\n- `identity` ✅\n- `name` ✅\n- `shortName` ✅\n- `sourceName` ✅\n- `tags` ✅\n\n**Issues I see:**\n1. Missing `$schema` - recommended for validation\n2. Missing `preferNameDirectory` - nice to have\n\n\n3. Missing `groupIdentity` - this is actually critical for handling template updates on NuGet\n4. The `defaultValue: \"net9.0\"` aligns with the available choices, so that's fine\n5. No `precedence` field - matters when multiple template versions exist\n6. No `description` field - won't show in `dotnet new list` but useful metadata\n\nThe real gap for NuGet publishing is the packaging configuration itself, which lives outside template.json. Within the template file though, `groupIdentity` and `precedence` are the most important missing pieces for proper versioning and updates.","outputTokens":536,"requestId":"33D6:256A51:1E53388:222D2C8:69E81B4E"},"id":"2bbe5eb7-1143-4e99-8a99-cfdc9228aca8","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:50:33.839Z","parentId":"42ab0f29-b783-49ae-9b43-9319d4f4d7e4"}
