{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f1d12ca2-e21c-478f-93e3-b58091e65977","content":"Here's my assessment — the template is **not quite ready** to publish. The JSON is valid and covers the basics, but there are a few gaps:\n\n**Critical:**\n- **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Without this, NuGet can't properly track template updates across versions. Add something like `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`.\n- **No packaging project** — There's no `.csproj` or `.nuspec` to actually produce a `.nupkg`. You'll need a `<PackageType Include=\"Template\" />` project to pack and push to NuGet.\n\n**Recommended:**\n- **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for IDE validation support.\n- **No `description`** — Helps discoverability on NuGet and in `dotnet new search`.\n- **Consider `preferNameDirectory: true`** — Standard for project templates.\n\n**Looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, `sourceName`, and the `Framework` symbol are all well-formed.\n\nWant me to fix these issues?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8cf20ffd-3edf-421c-bc41-efed87f298de","outputTokens":274,"requestId":"33D6:256A51:1E55490:222F9BE:69E81B59"},"id":"a70590c5-4fe2-410d-aeb3-5e9a12c09928","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:50:41.585Z","parentId":"c1f797c3-87b2-4223-8e5f-6d797484afd0"}
